{{wikipedia|Sakha language|Yakut language}}
===Etymology===
From {{der|en|ru|яку́т}}, from {{der|en|trk-pro|*yaka|t=collar; edge}}. Related to [[:w:Yakut language|Yakut]] {{m|sah|саха}} via earlier *''čaqa'' < *''ǰaqa''. Compare {{cog|tr|yaka||collar}}. The ending -ут possibly contains the Mongol plural suffix; compare {{nc|bua|яхад|tr=jаẋаd|t=Yakuts}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/jəˈkuːt/|/jəˈkʊt/}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|Yakut}}
# One of a [[Siberian]] people who speak a [[Turkic]] language, and live in the [[Lena]] river basin.
===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# The [[language]] of these people.
